title: 78: Cicero's "On Doody" 3: Buyer Beware
dc:creator: A.J. Hanenburg
description: The third part of Cicero's "On Duty" doesn't fail to disappoint. Or, at least, it wasn't what A.J. was expecting going in. On the other hand, we get to go through some fun moral cases involving vermin, grain, and two drowning wise men having discussions about boards.
itunes:author: Author: Who cares? I hope they get hit by cars.
itunes:subtitle: Why Graeme and A.J. would make terrible businessmen.
